    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-12-01T22:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-12-01T22:00:00-05:00" n="1226"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1226">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 867.00/722</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MH1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morgenthau</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <dateline>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-12-01T22:00:00-05:00">
                        <hi rend="italic">December 1, 1914, 10 p.m.</hi>
                    </date>
                </dateline>
                <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                <p>90. Your despatch 120, October 5.<note n="1" xml:id="d1226fn1">Not
                        printed.</note> Department forwarded to the Navy Department copy of circular
                        <hi rend="italic">note verbale</hi> from the Sublime Porte and has received
                    a reply from the Navy Department suggesting in view of the limitations placed
                    upon the cruising ground of naval vessels in Turkish waters by the terms of this
                    note, that the American Ambassador be asked his opinion as to whether under the
                        <pb facs="1089" n="775" xml:id="pg_775"/> circumstances one of the two
                    United States warships now in Ottoman waters might be returned to the United
                    States. Each vessel was sent to Europe hurriedly, and is in need of docking and
                    repair.</p>
                <p>Please report to Department.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BWJ1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
